{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"aa45d5bc-332d-47e8-b8c7-b268942e5703","content":"You can filter by class name using the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nOr more precisely by class:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"ClassName=ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nIf you need to specify the project too:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so it matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8aa3d1c9-b407-405c-b89a-3074a2a6b2b6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. Let me check the test files to give accurate advice.","outputTokens":190,"requestId":"1BCB:1521A3:6C85311:7520387:6A03D4C8"},"id":"b47f37ca-8635-4993-8ba6-deb1ff3683ab","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:33:01.469Z","parentId":"96126039-b1c7-4e63-b9e7-59a0b7ae8862"}
